          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch9ToDecimal",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a specific type of numeric representation known as \"overpunch\" into a decimal format. Overpunch is a technique used in mainframe systems to encode the sign of a number within the last digit of a numeric string. This function interprets such strings and returns a decimal value that accurately reflects the intended numeric value, including its sign."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
